==English==

=== Etymology ===
Comes from Middle English ''[[melancolie]]'', from Late Latin ''[[melancholia]]'', from Greek ''[[μελαγχολία]]'', from ''[[μέλας]]'', ''[[μελαν-]]'', "black", + ''[[χολή]]'', "bile."

=== Adjective ===
'''melancholy'''

#Affected with great sadness or depression.

